Report the current status of your work. The status appears in the channel's status block. Keep statuses concise (1-2 sentences) and informative. Use kind "progress" (default) for intermediate updates. Use kind "outcome" ONLY when ALL parts of the task have reached a terminal result — you must signal an outcome before finishing, but signaling prematurely (before every step is complete) is a critical error that causes the task to be reported as done when it isn't.